        <h1><B>The Toolkit:</B></h1>
        <p>The toolkit is a text-based experimental resource for carrying out experiments on dialogue. The chat tool provides a way of intercepting participants' typed turns and selectively interfering with both their content and timing. This allows very fine-grained experimental control over what participants perceive the other participants as having typed.</p>
        <p>The chat tool includes a constantly expanding library of experiments that can be reconfigured. It also provides an extensive API for programming experimental interventions that are sensitive to the conversational context of the participants. Watch this <A HREF = "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H_ZmjBoEOLQ">video</A> to see a demonstration of how the chat tool works.  There is also a list of references below, which describes some of the experimental setups that use the chat tool methodology. For a deeper discussion, please read this<A HREF = "http://homepages.inf.ed.ac.uk/gmills/MillsHealey2013Submission.pdf"> paper.</A></p>
 


